Package: CRPClustering
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian Nonparametric Chinese Restaurant Process Clustering with Entropy
Version: 1.0
Date: 2018-01-20
Authors@R: c(
  person("Masashi", "Okada", role = c("aut", "cre"), email="okadaalgorithm@gmail.com")
  )
Maintainer: Masashi Okada <okadaalgorithm@gmail.com>
Description: Chinese Restaurant Process is used in order to compose Dirichlet Process. The clustering which use Chinese Restaurant Process does not need to decide a number of clusters in advance. This algorithm automatically adjusts it. And this package calculates ambiguity as entropy.
Depends: R (>= 3.4.2)
License: GPL (>= 2)
Imports: MASS, mvtnorm, randomcoloR, graphics, stats, utils, png
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Suggests: knitr, rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
